org.openhab.binding.lcn.logic.data

Enum LCNSyntax.Command

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<LCNSyntax.Command>
      • org.openhab.binding.lcn.logic.data.LCNSyntax.Command
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<LCNSyntax.Command>
    Enclosing class:
    LCNSyntax

    public static enum LCNSyntax.Command
extends java.lang.Enum<LCNSyntax.Command>
    This enum represents the type of command.
    Commands followed by a '?' are not implemented yet.
    ON = Switch ON
    OFF = Switch OFF
    DI = Dim
    DIV = The Dim value of the lamp
    TA = Toggle
    AD = Add to Dim
    SB = Subtract from Dim
    FL = Flicker
    TH = Timed
    MT = Memory button
    RS = Ramp stop
    TE = Timed (preserving)
    AY = Dim all outlets
    AE = Activate all outlets
    AA = Deactivate all outlets
    AU = Toggle all outlets
    AH = Set brightness for all outlets
    ST, KT = Quick timer ?
    AB = Limit outlet
    JE = Shutter
    DL = DALI ?
    DLX = DALI raw ?
    SZ = Save/load light scene
    SZW = Choose register of light scene
    SZD = Write light scene directly
    SZR = Read light scene directly
    R8 = External relay
    R8T = Quick timer for external relay
    R8M = Engine positioning
    TS = Send button
    TV = Delayed send button
    TX = Lock button
    TXZA = Timelock button
    LA = Control LED
    SMT = LED status request
    MW = Report data
    MWO = Report data (old firmware)
    ZA = Add counter
    ZS = Subtract counter
    RE = Set controller
    SP = Repeat threshold
    SL1 = List thresholds
    SS = Move threshold
    SSO = Move threshold (old firmware)
    NM = Request name of bus module
    NMO = Request/Set OEM-text of a bus module
    NMOS = Set text of bus module
    SN = Request serial number
    SK = Search all segment couplers
    PM = Programming mode ?
    GD = Dynamic groups
    PI = Beep
    SM = Status request
    GTDT = Dynamic text
    GTDD = Timed dynamic text
    MR = LCN-MRS
    IL = Change language for I-port
    BINARY = Binary sensor
    Since:
    1.7.0
    Author:
    Patrik Pastuschek
